    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A double-crust apple pie needs a pastry that stays crisp under a juicy filling. All-butter shortcrust at a 2:1 flour-to-fat ratio does this. Bramley apples break down quickly in the oven, which is what the pie needs; dessert apples stay too firm. The ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "steam vent",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "term": "steam vent",
                  "termId": "cmpbjwuc00000s0v4aprwvpfh"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " in the lid is not optional.",
            "type": "text"
          }
