            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold butter into the flour, salt, and sugar until the mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs. Add 4 to 5 tablespoons of cold water, one at a time, mixing with a knife until the dough just comes together. Divide into two thirds (for the base) and one third (for the lid). Flatten each into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare the filling and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 200°C conventional. Toss the sliced apples with both sugars, the spices, flour, and lemon juice. Roll the larger pastry disc to 3 mm thick and use it to line a 23 cm pie dish, leaving an overhang. Fill with the apple mixture, mounding slightly in the centre. Roll out the smaller disc and lay it over the filling. Trim the overhang to 1 cm, fold it under, and crimp the edges to seal. Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with caster sugar. Cut two or three slashes in the centre as a steam vent. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until deep golden brown and the filling is bubbling through the vents. Leave for 15 minutes before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
